  "fullDescription": "The Eleusinian Mysteries\nwere the most famous and revered secret religious rites of ancient Greece, celebrated for nearly two millennia at Eleusis near Athens.\nDedicated to Demeter and Persephone, these mystery initiations\npromised initiates (mystai) a blessed afterlife and revealed secret knowledge about death, rebirth, and the cycle of life.\nThe rites remained so sacred that their exact content was never fully disclosed, protected by oath of secrecy under penalty of death.\n\nHades, god of the underworld, seized Persephone (Kore) while she gathered flowers in a meadow. The earth opened and swallowed her into the realm of the dead.\n\nLocation: Nysa meadow (various traditions)",
